SPOT VS SHOT - PARKING LOT

Sometimes, the best photos come from unexpected locations. In this series, we’ll be exploring how to find the perfect spot for your shot. First up: how to find distraction-free spots with interesting light in the most mundane locations. We all know that finding the right location for a photoshoot is crucial, but sometimes we’re forced to work with less than ideal settings. Case in point: a parking lot plaza. Sure, there are plenty of cars and other distractions in the parking lot, but with the right eye and some creative thinking, you can turn even the most mundane of locations into the perfect backdrop for your photos.

#phototips #torontophotographer #lightmagic #torontoweddingphotographer

NICOLETTE & SANJAY - DESTINATION ENGAGEMENT

Looking back on this incredible engagement shoot we did with Nicolette and Sanjay in St. Maarten, we're reminded of the unique and unforgettable experiences that a destination shoot can offer. 

Not only does it allow you to escape the stresses of everyday life, but it also provides the perfect opportunity to create lasting memories with your significant other in a stunning and exotic location. By spending quality time with your photographer during a destination shoot, you'll be able to form a deeper connection that will translate into stunning, personalized photographs that perfectly capture your love story. 

For future clients considering a destination shoot, we highly recommend it as a way to make your engagement experience truly unforgettable.

#destinationengagement #exoticlocation #unforgettableexperience #torontoweddingphotographer #torontoengagementphotographer

SPOT vs SHOT - BUGS!

Don’t let unexpected circumstances ruin a good photo opportunity! 
During this engagement shoot, we were swarmed by thousands of bugs on our way back to the parking lot. 
They were everywhere, in our hair, on our clothes and even stuck on our clients lipgloss. 
But we didn’t let that stop us. 
With some creative thinking and a little bit of lighting, we turned the situation into a stunning shot. We dropped a strobe behind the couple and triggered it to light up the pesky buggers. 
Remember to expose for their skin and always be open to rolling with unsuspecting circumstances.
See every situation as an opportunity to create something special.

#phototips #lightmagic #torontophotographer #torontoweddingphotographer

FIND THE LIGHT - MIDNIGHT ON KING ST. 

Shooting at night without any of your own light sources can be intimidating. But I have a secret to share - it’s actually my favorite! ;)

As wedding photographers, we often rely on our flashes and LEDs to light up our subjects, and it’s necessary in our line of work. However, for me, always having full control of the light can sometimes feel monotonous. 

I love to stay fresh and inspired by pushing myself to think outside the box. Using the environment as my light source can take my imagery to a whole new level of inspiration.
We are constantly surrounded by interesting light sources - street lights, neon signs, restaurant lights, or even car headlights - all of which can make for unique and captivating lighting. 
We’re used to using these lights as ambient lighting to enhance the mood of our images, but don’t be afraid to also use them as your MAIN light.

Let me share a story and a shot from a recent wedding we photographed for Anjali & Justin at the Ritz Carlton in Toronto. 
As wedding photographers, we always strive for variety in our imagery to tell a compelling story in our albums. So, whenever we have a chance, we take our couples for additional creative shots at different times of the day. 
Being downtown on King St, we found an interesting building directory kiosk with rotating advertisements. Some of the ads were vibrant and colorful, so we patiently waited for a cleaner surface to display itself.
When using a flat uni-directional light source like this, it’s important to remember to create flattering light for both the bride and the groom. In this case, using split light to short side light worked perfectly. Once the light on the couple was just right, we posed them sweetly and voila!

The result was a gorgeous image with a beautifully lit-up couple. It’s important to be quick though, as the ads change rapidly. ;)

Let me know what you think and if you’d like more of these types of tips in the comment section below. Thanks! <3 

At the time of this shoot I didn’t take any BTS of the kind at location.  King st stock shot credit: Ken Lund

Here is a glimpse into one of the most extraordinary weddings of the year.
Our couple, Kyle and Erik, adorned themselves in the most spectacular suits and radiated in sheer style. Their fashion-forward choices were truly the centrepiece of an unforgettable celebration.

The team at Ro Creative Company curated this day to perfection! From the breathtaking florals by Royal Orchid Florals to the beautiful venue at Graydon Hall, every detail came together seamlessly. 

But it wasn't just the visual creativity that made this day remarkable - Kyle and Erik's genuine chemistry and natural charm shone through in every frame. Their trust in me to capture their most important day is a gift I will always cherish.

As we look back on this weekend’s grand affair, we're reminded that love knows no bounds and that dreams do come true.
Join us in celebrating Kyle and Erik's love story and stay tuned for the full wedding reel, where you'll witness every special moment of this incredible celebration.

SONIA + SASHA 

It was an amazing honour to have the opportunity to photograph this wedding. 
My friendship with Sonia spans several years from our shared work in the bridal industry. For those who may not be familiar with Sonia, she is renowned as one of the top wedding planners worldwide, so you can imagine the meticulous care and passion that went into every detail of this magical week-long wedding celebration. 

There are so many images to share from all the events, but I wanted to begin with this soft gorgeous image of her on the morning of her ceremony day. There’s an extraordinary and poignant moment when you’ve worked alongside someone in the same demanding trenches of the industry, and then you witness them stepping into the role of the bride. It’s a privilege I hold dear, and I’m immensely grateful for the opportunity to be a part of this beautiful journey. 

Thank you once again for entrusting me with such a significant role in your special day.
